  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nDealers are currently positioned in positive gamma territory (PIN regime) with SPX at 6531 sitting below the 6543 flip level, indicating they're likely buying this dip as systematic hedging flow while the massive +9.3B gamma wall at 6550 acts as a magnet. The 41.7% GEX surge signals heavy options flow just hit the market, creating a tight trading range between the 6500 put wall (-8.8B gamma amplification zone) and the 6550 call wall where dealers will aggressively sell any rally attempts. \n\nWatch for mean reversion back toward 6543-6550 as dealer buying pressure should provide support here, but any break below 6500 flips dealers short gamma and triggers accelerated selling into the void.",
